<title>POLAND: Polish parliament approves flood relief laws.</title>
<headline>Polish parliament approves flood relief laws.</headline>
<dateline>WARSAW 1997-07-17</dateline>
<text>
<p>Poland's lower house on Thursday approved laws to fund flood relief, including an amendment to the 1997 budget letting the government borrow more abroad and from the central bank, a parliament press office official said.</p>
<p>The budget amendment will increase by 2.5 billion zlotys the amount of treasury paper the government can sell directly to the central bank.</p>
<p>It also increases the limit on foreign borrowing to allow a $300 million soft loan Poland is seeking from the World Bank.</p>
